bug.short_desc: Fedora 25 on Raspberry Pi 3 randomly kernel panics
bug.cf_doc_type: If docs needed, set a value

long_desc.thetext:
Created attachment 1246571 Kernel Panoc catched
Description of problem:
Running Fedora 25 on a Raspberry Pi 3 (three) using kernel 4.9.5-200.fc25.armv7hl the server randomly crashes with a kernel panic. The previous kernel vmlinuz-4.9.3-200.fc25.armv7hl suffers the same.
Running the same installation on a Raspberry Pi 2 (two) by moving the SD card works fine.
Version-Release number of selected component (if applicable): cat /etc/redhat-release Fedora release 25 (Twenty Five)
How reproducible:
Steps to Reproduce: 1. Install Fedora on a Rapsberry Pi 3 2. Run dnf update to install all available patches 3. Wait. After some time the Pi will die... 4. Move sd card to Raspberry Pi 2; Pi will not die.
Actual results: Kernel Panic
Expected results: No Kernel Panic
Additional info: Seems like a kernel issue, the same Pi has been running for weeks without problem. After upgrading to kernel > vmlinuz-4.9.x problems seem to occur.
Some extra information: crashes looks like they're NOT related to the power supply; it's an "official Raspberry" one, 2.5A.
kernel-4.9.8-201.fc25 has been submitted as an update to Fedora 25. https://bodhi.fedoraproject.org/updates/FEDORA-2017-76e3fe6cfa

kernel-4.9.8-201.fc25 has been pushed to the Fedora 25 testing repository. If problems still persist, please make note of it in this bug report. See https://fedoraproject.org/wiki/QA:Updates_Testing for instructions on how to install test updates. You can provide feedback for this update here: https://bodhi.fedoraproject.org/updates/FEDORA-2017-76e3fe6cfa
